page.title: 17FAUNA OF HOLBERROW GREEN
page.content:
On the Feckenham Wylde Moor Nature Reserve there is a hide from which members of the Worcestershire Nature Conservation Trust and their visitors can enjoy the wildlife.
Here a few pairs of snipe breed regularly, reed buntings and owls nest and there has been a sighting of a bird which has come to Britain from France, the Cettis Warbler. Many birds of prey visit during the winter when several short-eared owls can be detected. Also regularly seen are Moorhen and Heron.
There is a large rookery in a small wood in Shurnock. Here there are up to 100 rooks' nests mainly situated in Oak Trees but also in Ash Trees.
